Design a detailed, phased project roadmap from the structured client requirements below. This plan
is shown to both the client and the delivery team, so be thorough, concrete, and well-sequenced.

Produce:
- summary: a 3-4 sentence overview of the overall execution strategy and what success looks like.
- objectives: 3-6 strategic objectives the roadmap must achieve, drawn from the client's goals.
- execution_strategy: a short paragraph (3-5 sentences) on HOW the work will be approached —
  sequencing, ways of working, what is front-loaded and why.
- phases: an ordered list of milestones. For each milestone provide:
  - name: short milestone title (e.g. "Phase 1 - Foundation")
  - description: what gets done and why, in 2-3 sentences
  - target_date: a sensible date or window IF the requirements imply a timeline; otherwise null
  - owner: the role or team accountable (e.g. "Design lead", "Engineering"); null if unclear
  - duration: a rough length or effort (e.g. "2 weeks"); null if timing is unspecified
  - deliverables: concrete outputs produced in this milestone
  - dependencies: names of earlier milestones (or inputs) this phase needs before it can start;
    empty list if none
- success_metrics: 3-6 measurable signals that show the project is on track or done.

Rules:
- Every service and goal in the requirements must be covered by at least one milestone.
- Sequence milestones logically (dependencies first; launch/marketing last).
- Respect the stated deadline, budget, and constraints. Do not invent scope or dates the
  requirements don't support. If timing is unspecified, leave target_date/duration null.

